---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import { recognition } from '../data/recognition';
---
<Layout title="Recognition — Shailesh Dudala" description="Team recognition and carefully attributed project contributions across healthcare interoperability and applied machine learning." canonicalPath="/recognition/">
  <section class="page-hero recognition-hero"><div class="shell recognition-hero-grid"><div><p class="eyebrow">Recognition</p><h1>The award matters. The attribution matters too.</h1></div><p>Recognition is supporting context for the engineering story. Team projects stay team projects, and individual contribution is stated only at the level the public record supports.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="shell recognition-page">
    <article class="award-feature" id="lets-talk-doc"><div class="award-number">01</div><div class="award-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Team recipient · 2025</p><h2>{recognition[0].title}</h2><h3>{recognition[0].project}</h3><p>Let’s Talk Doc explored standards-aware, multilingual post-visit communication. Shailesh’s current career record supports an AI video-avatar application contribution for follow-up and smart intake using FHIR/HL7 workflows. Official sources confirm the project and recipient list; they do not isolate component ownership.</p><div class="award-links"><a href={recognition[0].officialUrl}>Official winners announcement ↗</a><a href={recognition[0].recipientUrl}>Official recipient list ↗</a><a href={recognition[0].membershipUrl}>Team project context ↗</a></div></div><aside><span>Attribution</span><strong>Team recognition</strong><p>No claim of sole authorship, clinical deployment, or patient-outcome impact.</p></aside></article>
    <div class="recognition-grid">{recognition.slice(1).map((item, index) => <article><span>{String(index + 2).padStart(2, '0')}</span><p class="eyebrow">{item.attribution}</p><h2>{item.title}</h2><h3>{item.project}</h3><p>{item.evidence}</p>{'officialUrl' in item && item.officialUrl && <a href={item.officialUrl}>Public source ↗</a>}</article>)}</div>
  </div></section>
</Layout>
